  <td>Jobber</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
            </div>

            <div id="who-each-is-for" class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">Who Each Platform Is Built For</h2>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
                  <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Jobber</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70 mb-3">Built for small-to-mid home service businesses that need a simple, affordable platform to manage scheduling, invoicing, and customer communication.</p>
                  <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-foreground/80">
                    <li>• Solo operators to 15-tech teams</li>
                    <li>• Revenue: $200K–$3M/year</li>
                    <li>• Primarily residential service</li>
                    <li>• Owners who want to self-implement</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
                  <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">ServiceTitan</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70 mb-3">Built for mid-to-large residential and commercial HVAC companies that need enterprise-grade operations management, marketing analytics, and sales tools.</p>
                  <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-foreground/80">
                    <li>• 15-100+ technician teams</li>
                    <li>• Revenue: $3M–$50M+/year</li>
                    <li>• Residential + commercial mix</li>
                    <li>• Dedicated operations/office staff</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="scheduling" class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Scheduling & Dispatch</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Jobber's scheduling is clean and intuitive — drag-and-drop jobs onto a calendar, assign technicians, and send automated notifications. It handles the basics well and is fast to learn. ServiceTitan's dispatch board is significantly more advanced: it includes capacity planning, zone-based routing, technician skill matching, and real-time GPS tracking. For a 5-tech team, Jobber's simplicity is an advantage. For a 20-tech team with multiple service zones, ServiceTitan's dispatch capabilities become essential. <strong>Winner: ServiceTitan (for complex operations).</strong>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="crm-pipeline" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3">CRM & Sales Pipeline</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Jobber's Client Hub is excellent for customer self-service — clients can approve quotes, schedule appointments, and pay invoices online. The quote follow-up automation is solid for a small team. ServiceTitan goes much deeper: it offers a full sales pipeline with membership program management, equipment replacement tracking, financing integration, and detailed customer history. If you sell maintenance agreements or equipment replacements, ServiceTitan's CRM is in a different league. <strong>Winner: ServiceTitan.</strong>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="reporting" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Reporting & Analytics</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                This is where the gap between the two platforms is widest. Jobber provides standard KPI dashboards — revenue, job completion rates, outstanding invoices. Useful, but basic. ServiceTitan offers deep analytics including marketing attribution (which campaigns generate revenue, not just leads), technician performance scorecards, revenue per job type, membership program analytics, and custom report builders. If data-driven decision making is important to your growth strategy, ServiceTitan's reporting alone can justify the price difference. <strong>Winner: ServiceTitan (by a wide margin).</strong>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="pricing" class="mt-10">
