<!-- FAQ Section -->
<div id="faq" class="mt-10">
  <h2 class="font-semibold text-2xl mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="space-y-0">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Is ServiceTitan worth the price for a small HVAC company?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">For most companies under 10 technicians, no. ServiceTitan's per-technician pricing ($200-300+/month per tech) makes it prohibitively expensive for small teams. The ROI only makes sense when you have enough revenue and call volume to justify the advanced reporting and marketing features. Jobber at $39-249/month total is a much better fit for small operations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Can Jobber scale as my HVAC company grows?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Jobber can comfortably handle teams up to 15-20 technicians on the Grow plan ($249/month). Beyond that, you may start hitting limitations in reporting depth, marketing attribution, and workflow complexity. Many companies start with Jobber and migrate to ServiceTitan when they reach 15-25+ techs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">How long does it take to implement ServiceTitan?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">ServiceTitan implementation typically takes 6-12 weeks with dedicated onboarding support. This includes data migration, team training, workflow configuration, and integration setup. Jobber can be set up in 1-3 days for basic operations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Does Jobber have a pricebook like ServiceTitan?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Jobber has a basic pricebook for creating estimates and invoices, but it is not as sophisticated as ServiceTitan's pricebook which includes flat-rate pricing, equipment databases, and dynamic pricing rules. If flat-rate pricing is critical to your operation, ServiceTitan has a significant advantage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Can I try both before committing?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Jobber offers a 14-day free trial with no credit card required. ServiceTitan does not offer a free trial — you need to book a demo and go through a sales process. This is one reason we recommend starting with Jobber if you are unsure.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="article-section" style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-muted, #f8f9fa); border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary, #1B4F72);">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">The Bigger Question: Who Answers at 9pm?</h3>
  <p>Both Jobber and ServiceTitan handle jobs once they're booked. The bigger question: who answers the phone at 9pm when a homeowner's A/C dies? Compare <a href="/hvac/answering-service/ai-vs-traditional-answering-service">traditional vs AI answering services for HVAC</a> to see what's changed in 2026.</p>
</div>

